<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="203" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1350,1737]" pageId="8" pageNumber="203">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Monne, M. A. &amp; Martins, U. R." box="[309,600,1350,1377]" pageId="8" pageNumber="203" pagination="43 - 98" refId="ref10439" refString="Monne, M. A. &amp; Martins, U. R. (1976) Contribuicao ao conhecimento dos Acanthocinini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae). Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 30 (4), 43 - 98." type="journal article" year="1976">Monné &amp; Martins (1976)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Monne &amp; Martins, 1976" authorityName="Monne &amp; Martins" authorityYear="1976" box="[613,1069,1350,1376]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Paranisopodus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[613,783,1350,1376]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="203">Paranisopodus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Monne, M. A. &amp; Martins, U. R." box="[792,1069,1350,1376]" pageId="8" pageNumber="203" pagination="43 - 98" refId="ref10439" refString="Monne, M. A. &amp; Martins, U. R. (1976) Contribuicao ao conhecimento dos Acanthocinini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae). Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 30 (4), 43 - 98." type="journal article" year="1976">Monné &amp; Martins, 1976</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="White, 1855" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anisopodus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1222,1353,1350,1376]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="203">Anisopodus</emphasis>
White, 1855
</taxonomicName>
, by the antennomere III distinctly elongate, and the following gradually shorter, lateral tubercle of the prothorax perpendicular and placed about posterior third, presence of tubercles on pronotum, elytral centro basal crest distinctly elevated, presence of tubercles on elytra, and inner apical projection in metatarsomere I. We find some of these features to be variable in species currently placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="White" authorityYear="1855" box="[834,965,1494,1520]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anisopodus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[834,965,1494,1520]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="203">Anisopodus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the general shape of the lateral prothoracic tubercles makes transference of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1865" box="[646,857,1530,1556]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anisopodus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acutus">
<emphasis box="[646,857,1530,1556]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="203">Anisopodus acutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Monne &amp; Martins" authorityYear="1976" box="[893,1063,1530,1556]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Paranisopodus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[893,1063,1530,1556]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="203">Paranisopodus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appropriate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1350,1737]" pageId="8" pageNumber="203">
The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nascimento &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[347,599,1566,1592]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Paranisopodus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acutus">
<emphasis box="[347,599,1566,1592]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="203">Paranisopodus acutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recently redescribed and illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Santos-Silva, A. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. &amp; Le Tirant, S." box="[1105,1399,1566,1592]" pageId="8" pageNumber="203" pagination="139 - 145" refId="ref10642" refString="Santos-Silva, A., Galileo, M. H. M. &amp; Le Tirant, S. (2017) A new species of Cirrhicera Thomson, 1857 from Mexico, and redescription of Anisopodus acutus Thomson, 1865 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae. Zootaxa, 4323 (1), 139 - 145. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4323.1.12" type="journal article" year="2017">
Santos-Silva 
<emphasis box="[1255,1314,1566,1592]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="203">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1865" box="[151,363,1602,1628]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anisopodus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acutus">
<emphasis box="[151,363,1602,1628]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="203">Anisopodus acutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Gérard Luc Tavakilian (MNHN; personal communication) confirmed that the tubercles in the metaventrite are present in the 
<typeStatus box="[498,596,1638,1664]" pageId="8" pageNumber="203">holotype</typeStatus>
and are very evident. This feature allows confirming that the redescription of the species was based on a specimen correctly identified.
</paragraph>
